 "title": "Onion marmalade – lovely with everything",
 "excerpt": "I always buy the little bottle of onion marmalade at the shop and eat it with cheese, chops on bread and just about anything because I love it so much. So I decided to make my own. Nothing difficult, just time-consuming. YOU NEED: 2kg onions sliced into thin rings …",
 "seo": {
  "title": "Onion marmalade - lovely with everything - Marinda Kook",
  "description": null
 },
 "html": "<p>I always buy the little bottle of onion marmalade at the shop and eat it with cheese, chops on bread and just about anything because I love it so much.  So I decided to make my own.  Nothing difficult, just time-consuming.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-061.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1596\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 061\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-061-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>YOU NEED:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2kg onions sliced into thin rings<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-023.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1579\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 023\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-023-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>100 ml oil</li>\n<li>500 ml balsamic vinegar</li>\n<li>500 ml red wine</li>\n<li>500 g brown sugar<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-036.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1584\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 036\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-036-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>salt and pepper</li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOW:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>peel the onions and slice into rings<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-030.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1581\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 030\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-030-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a> and fry until glossy in oil<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-043.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1586\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 043\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-043-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl and pour over the onions<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-049.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1587\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 049\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-049-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>now cook for 60 to 90 minutes until the sauce becomes syrupy – cook without a lid<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-056.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1589\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 056\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-056-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>pour into sterilised bottles and store<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-068.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1592\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 068\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-068-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Just look, these tangy little onions on a burger or a cheese board taste amazing.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-0631.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1593\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 26052014 063\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-26052014-0631-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
}
